'''Salome Samadashvili''' (Georgian: სალომე სამადაშვილი; fanau ia 2 Aperila 1976) o se tagata polokiki a Georgia o ia o le United National Movement Member o le Palemene o Georgia. E tolu taimi sa avea ai o ia ma totino o le Palemene o Georgia (2004, 2016, 2020).

==Talaaga==
Salome Samadashvili na fanau ia Aperila 2, 1976. Na faauu mai le Allegheny College, Central European University ma American University of Washington. Mai le 1994 i le 1995 sa avea o ia ma faʻaliliuupu ma fesoasoani i le polokalama a le US National Democratic Institute. I le 1997-1998 sa avea o ia ma tagata suʻesuʻe i Herbert Scoville International Research Center i Montana. 1998 - Ulu o Chancellery i le Amepasa o Georgia i le US. I le 1999-2001 sa avea o ia ma polofesa Lagolago o le Iunivesite a Amerika o Uosigitone, 2000-2001 - Carana Corporation Legal Consultant, 2001-2002 - Washington International Education and Arts Center Program Specialist, 2002-2004 - US National Head of the Parliamentary Program of the Democratic Inisitituti (Georgia, Kazakhstan), 2004-2005 - i le sui lona 6 o le Palemene, 2005-2007 - Amepasa Tele ma le Amepasa Amepasa o le Netherlands, Amepasa Extra talagsaon ma Plenipotentiary o le Malo o Peleseuma ma le Grand Duchy o Luxembourg ma le Europa Union o le ulu o le misiona. I le 2013-2014 o ia o le Honorary Visiting Fellow o le Wilfred Martens Center mo Europa Studies, ma i le 2015 Faatonu o le Libyan Governance Program i le US National Democratic Institute (Malta-Tripoli, Libya). Talu mai le 2016 o ia o le faʻavae ma Ofisa Sili o Pulega o le NGO Center mo Strategic Communication and Democracy ma consulting firm Samadashvili International Consultants. Salome Samadashvili o se faiaoga aʻoaʻoina i le Iunivesite o Georgia ma Ilia Chavchavadze State University. Talu mai Me 5, 2016, ua avea o ia ma Ulu o le Matagaluega o Faʻavaomalo Vafealoai ma Faʻaupufai Saienisi i le Iunivesite o Georgia. Sa avea o ia ma totino o le Fono Faitulafono a le Palemene o Georgia talu mai Novema 2016. I le 2017, o loʻo ia te ia le tofiga o le Sui Taʻitaʻifono o le vaega a le Palemene "National Movement".
